{
  "title": "Steppers",
  "href": "http://www.google.com/design/spec/components/steppers.html",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "intro",
      "html": "<p>Steppers convey progress through numbered steps. They may also be used for navigation.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "article-list",
      "articles": [
        {
          "type": "article",
          "title": "Usage",
          "modules": [
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Steppers display progress through a sequence by breaking it up into multiple logical and numbered steps.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B7WCemMG6e0Vb2hCdkt3d05DVUE/components_acux_stepper_vertstep.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Steppers should be used when a field determines a subsequent field.</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "text",
                      "src": "<p><strong>Active stepper circle </strong></p><ul><li>24dp x 24dp</li><li>12sp Roboto Regular</li><li>Inherits primary color</li><li>Default color is Google Blue 500</li></ul><p><strong>Active step </strong></p><ul><li>14sp Roboto Medium</li><li>87% black</li></ul><p><strong>Connector line </strong></p><ul><li>1dp border</li><li>Grey 400 color value</li></ul>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "text",
                      "src": "<p><strong>Inactive stepper circle</strong></p><ul><li>24dp x 24dp</li><li>12sp Roboto Regular</li><li>100% white</li><li>Grey 500 color value</li></ul><p><strong>Inactive steps</strong></p><ul><li>14sp Roboto Regular</li><li>26% black</li></ul>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Avoid using steppers to break up sections in a short form, or multiple times on one page.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bzhp5Z4wHba3cWROeVk5LXhsczg/components_acux_stepper_avoid.png",
                      "caption": "<div class=\"caption-title\">Don&apos;t.</div><p>Don&#x2019;t embed steppers within steppers or use multiple steppers on one page.</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "article",
          "title": "Types of steps",
          "modules": [
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<h4>Editable steps</h4><p>Editable steps allow users to return later to edit a step. These are ideal for workflows that involve editing steps within a session.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bzhp5Z4wHba3WXRuZUhQVGZ1MFE/components_acux_stepper_editable.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Editable steps can be edited within a session.</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<h4>Non-editable steps</h4><p>Non-editable steps should be used when:</p><ul><li>Users cannot edit a step later </li><li>Step editing poses a distraction risk to form completion</li></ul>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bzhp5Z4wHba3Z3BmaTdNQTZvN28/components_acux_stepper_noneditable.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Non-editable steps cannot be edited once completed. </p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<h4>Mobile steps</h4>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B7WCemMG6e0VdkdHZl9FNDV6R28/components_acux_stepper_mbltypog.png",
                      "caption": "<p><strong>Mobile step text</strong></p><p>Steps displayed at the top in text</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B7WCemMG6e0VZV9JT1hKVjJwcFE/components_acux_stepper_mbldots.png",
                      "caption": "<p><strong>Mobile step dots</strong></p><p>Use dots when the number of steps isn&#x2019;t large</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B7WCemMG6e0VTUlvaXVPZEJ2LUU/components_acux_stepper_mblprgrssbr.png",
                      "caption": "<p><strong>Mobile step progress bar</strong></p><p>Use a progress bar when there are many steps, or if there are steps that need to be inserted during the process (based on responses to earlier steps).</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<h4>Optional steps</h4><p>Optional steps within a linear flow should be marked as optional.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B7WCemMG6e0VZDNSY2lFWWdDWm8/components_acux_stepper_optstps.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Mark optional steps in linear flows as optional.</p><p><strong>Optional steps</strong></p><ul><li>12sp Roboto Regular</li><li>54% black</li></ul>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "article",
          "title": "Types of steppers",
          "modules": [
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Horizontal steppers are ideal when the contents of one step depend on an earlier step. </p><p>Avoid using long step names in horizontal steppers.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B7WCemMG6e0VRUxaWWRqVXU5aGc/components_acux_stepper_horizstep.png",
                      "caption": "<p>On horizontal steppers, the step name and numbers appear on a horizontal bar, which can be fixed to the top of the page when scrolling down. </p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Horizontal steppers"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Vertical steppers are designed for narrow screen sizes. They are ideal for mobile.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0Bzhp5Z4wHba3WHFoTnI5cy11U1E/components_acux_stepper_mblvertinpg.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Vertical steppers can be used in mobile as-is. Simply ensure the contents for each step are responsive. </p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Vertical steppers"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Linear steppers require users to complete one step in order to move on to the next.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B7WCemMG6e0VOFVjMHV2TWdOMnM/components_acux_stepper_linear.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Each linear step must be completed before proceeding to the next one.</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Linear steppers"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Non-linear steppers allow users to enter a multi-step flow at any point.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B7WCemMG6e0VaXlOV1dLTk11dnc/components_acux_stepper_nonlinear.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Non-linear steps may be completed in any order.</p><p><strong>Inactive stepper circle</strong></p><ul><li>24dp x 24dp</li><li>12sp Roboto Regular</li><li>100% white</li><li>Grey 400 color value</li></ul><p><strong>Inactive steps</strong></p><ul><li>14sp Roboto Regular</li><li>54% black</li></ul>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Non-linear steppers"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B7WCemMG6e0VeEZhNnRLN2VlNG8/components_acux_stepper_altlblplcmnt.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Alternative label placement</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Alternative labels"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B7WCemMG6e0VTVpuUmNUSUhRZTA/components_acux_stepper_altlblplcmntoptstp.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Alternative label placement with optional step </p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Steppers may display a transient feedback message after a step is saved.  Stepper feedback should only be used if there is a long latency between steps.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "video",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B7WCemMG6e0VVFVRWklzeEFDSzA/components_acux_stepper_feedback.webm",
                      "caption": "<p>This stepper displays a transient feedback message after a step is saved.</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Stepper feedback"
            }
          ]
        },
